properties.description: Heavy rainfall is starting to gradually ease between Albany and Denmark, but damaging winds have now developed.  Weather Situation: A slow moving trough has been causing heavy rainfall over the South Coastal district, particularly near the Albany area. A low has developed in the trough just to the northwest of Albany, resulting in potentially damaging wind gusts in the area.  DAMAGING WINDS with gusts to 100 kilometres per hour are possible and could cause DAMAGE TO HOMES AND PROPERTY. These winds are most likely to occur around the Albany area, and should continue through Sunday evening before gradually easing after midnight.  HEAVY RAINFALL which may lead to FLASH FLOODING has been occurring from Albany to Denmark. The rainfall intensity is starting to ease, but flooding may persist for the next few hours.  Locations which may be affected include Albany and Denmark.  A wind gust of 89 km/h was recorded at Albany AIrport at 8:22pm.  51.2 mm has been recorded in the 6 hours to 7pm AWST at Denmark.  Significant flooding has been reported in the Albany area.
